Sarah C. Conland, president and owner of The Catskill Daily Mail and The Greene County News since 1979, died Sunday at her home here.

She was 71 years old.

Mrs. Conland was also president of Recorder Publications in Greenfield, Mass., publisher of The Greenfield (Mass.) Recorder. She was the wife of Henry Conland, who was president and publisher of The Daily Mail and The News from 1961 until his death in 1979. He had been co-publisher of The Recorder.

Mrs. Conland was a graduate of Smith College and had published several works of fiction.

Surviving are a son, Henry, of Storrs, Conn.; three grandchildren; a brother, and a sister.